<section class="brier-section">
  <h2>Brier Score Comparison</h2>

  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Model</th>
          <th>TEAM_ONLY</th>
          <th>SP_ENHANCED</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Logistic Regression</td>
          <td>0.2374</td>
          <td class="best">0.2331</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Random Forest</td>
          <td>0.2383</td>
          <td>0.2342</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>XGBoost</td>
          <td>0.2397</td>
          <td>0.2349</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="market-row">
          <td>Kalshi Market</td>
          <td>0.2434</td>
          <td>&mdash;</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p class="caption">
    Lower Brier score = better calibration. Scores computed via walk-forward backtest on
    2015&ndash;2024 data. Kalshi market Brier computed on 2,128 common 2025 games.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .brier-section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  th,
  td {
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a35;
  }

  th {
    color: #d4a843;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    border-bottom: 2px solid #d4a843;
  }

  td {
    color: #c0bdb8;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  tr:hover {
    background: rgba(212, 168, 67, 0.05);
  }

  .best {
    color: #d4a843;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .market-row {
    border-top: 2px solid #2a2a35;
  }

  .market-row td {
    color: #8a8880;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .caption {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #8a8880;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
